What is a Bean?
    â€¢ A Bean is simply a Java object managed by Spring.
    â€¢ Spring container is responsible for creating, configuring, and managing Beans.
Spring Containers:
    1. BeanFactory
        â—¦ Basic container
        â—¦ Provides lazy-loading of beans
        â—¦ Lightweight
       BeanFactory factory = new XmlBeanFactory(new FileSystemResource("beans.xml"));
    2. ApplicationContext
        â—¦ Advanced container
        â—¦ Supports events, AOP, internationalization, annotations
        â—¦ Eagerly loads beans by default
       ApplicationContext context = new ClassPathXmlApplicationContext("beans.xml");
       MyBean bean = context.getBean(MyBean.class);
Summary: Use ApplicationContext for modern apps.

